SIMPLE: when
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: When
<hw>When</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>when</ets>,
<ets>whan</ets>, <ets>whenne</ets>, <ets>whanne</ets>, AS.
<ets>hw⟦ae⟧nne</ets>, <ets>hwanne</ets>, <ets>hwonne</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>hwan</ets>, OD. <ets>wan</ets>, OHG. <ets>wanne</ets>, G.
<ets>wann</ets> when, <ets>wenn</ets> if, when, Goth. <ets>hwan</ets>
when, and to E. <ets>who</ets>. <?/<?/<?/<?/. See
<er>Who</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>At what time; -- used interrogatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>When</qex> shall these things be?</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xxiv.
3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ See the Note under <er>What</er>, <xex>pron</xex>.,
1.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At what time; at, during, or after the time that; at
or just after, the moment that; -- used relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kings may⟦br⟧
Take their advantage <qex>when</qex> and how they list.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Book lore ne'er served, <qex>when</qex> trial came,⟦br⟧
Nor gifts, <qex>when</qex> faith was dead.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>While; whereas; although; -- used in the manner of a
conjunction to introduce a dependent adverbial sentence or clause,
having a causal, conditional, or adversative relation to the principal
proposition; <as>as, he chose to turn highwayman <ex>when</ex> he might
have continued an honest man; he removed the tree <ex>when</ex> it was
the best in the grounds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Which time; then; -- used elliptically as a
noun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was adopted heir by his consent;⟦br⟧
Since <qex>when</qex>, his oath is broke.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>When</xex> was formerly used as an exclamation of
surprise or impatience, like <xex>what</xex>!</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Come hither; mend my ruff:⟦br⟧
Here, <qex>when</qex>! thou art such a tedious lady!</q> <rj><qau>J.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>When as</b></col>, <col><b>When
that</b></col></mcol>, <cd>at the time that; when.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>When as</qex> sacred light began to dawn.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>When that</qex> mine eye is famished for a look.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whenas</ent>⟦br⟧
